<section id="goal" data-brand-section class="melis-section">
  <div class="melis-section-eyebrow-row">
    <span class="num">03</span>
    <span class="name">Goal · the three-year horizon</span>
    <span class="line"></span>
  </div>
  <h2 class="melis-section-title">By the end of 2028, melis.ai is <em>the operator's reference</em> for AI education.</h2>

  <div class="melis-prose">
    <p>Goals exist to make decisions easier today. This is the picture three years out — concrete enough to test against, specific enough to disqualify the wrong opportunities. Every "should we…?" runs through this filter first.</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="melis-quote">
    <p>"The reference brand is the one operators check before they build, the one teachers cite before they teach, and the one peers point to when explaining what good looks like in this field."</p>
    <cite>Working definition · 2026.04.28</cite>
  </blockquote>

  <div class="melis-prose">
    <p>By the end of 2028:</p>
    <ul class="melis-ul">
      <li><strong>50,000+ students</strong> across the catalogue (Udemy already past 20,000).</li>
      <li><strong>The Claude Cowork Course</strong> is the field's reference onboarding for building a personal AI operation — quoted, taught, copied.</li>
      <li><strong>A thriving Skool community</strong> of operators teaching each other — not a content broadcast, a peer network.</li>
      <li><strong>The Dispatch</strong> is the newsletter operators forward to other operators.</li>
      <li><strong>YouTube channel</strong> doing essay-grade work, not how-to slop — at meaningful scale.</li>
      <li><strong>Dreamwith</strong> — the platform that productises the whole flywheel — in private beta or shipped.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="melis-aside">Updated annually. If we hit any of these early, we sharpen the goal — we don't soften it.</p>
  </div>
</section>
